///**************************************************************************************
///      CORRECT USAGE:
///**************************************************************************************
///
///  Calibre version v2017.2_16.14 is used to develop and QA this command file.
///  Please use Calibre v2017.2_16.14 or newer TSMC qualified version.
///
///  TSMC developed this deck using Mentor Graphics proprietary SVRF and TVF formats.
///  The deck is to be used only in Calibre tools.
///
///  To properly use this insertion tool, please read the following comments for the
///  options and set the switches correctly in the header for your design.
///
///  (1) #DEFINE UseprBoundary :
///      #DEFINE ChipWindowUsed :
///      The utility will use the boundary generated by defined (tape-out) layers
///      for the insertion by default.
///
///      If user wants to specify the window of chip by prBoundary(108) layer,
///      please un-comment the line as below:
///
///          #DEFINE UseprBoundary
///
///      If user want to specified the window of chip exactly, please un-comment
///      the line as below:
///
///          #DEFINE ChipWindowUsed
///
///      Then modify the Variables ( xLB, yLB ) for the coordinate of left-bottom corner
///      and ( xRT, yRT ) for the coordinate of right-top corner of the user-defined chip window
///      Moreover, the line below is an un-used layer number for constructing the chip window
///          LAYER ChipWindow 500
///      If layer number 500 is used, please assign another layer number without conflct.
///
///  (2) #DEFINE dmOnCorner :
///      The utility will not insert dummy layers in the chip corners and reserve the
///      space for sealring by default.
///      If user want to add dummy inside whole layout extent like sub-cell or macro
///      level applications, please un-comment the line as below:
///
///          #DEFINE dmOnCorner
///
///      For cell and macro level design, please turn on "dmOnCorner" to insert dummy on corner.
///
///  (3) #DEFINE WithSealring :
///      By default, this option is disabled for layout without sealring structure.
///      If the target layout for dummy pattern insertion already has the sealring,
///      users need to enable this option. The dummy patterns would be only inserted
///      inside the region that was shrinked "24um" inward. This could solve the overlap
///      between dummy patterns and assembly isoaltion regions.
///      Please un-comment the line as below to enable this option:
///
///      #DEFINE WithSealring
///
///  (4) #DEFINE USE_AREF :
///      #DEFINE USE_AUTOREF :
/// 	 By default, USE_AREF option is enabled to use aref structure in the output gds for file size
///      reduction. You can also enable USE_AUTOREF opion to reduce file size further by creation of
///      new hierarchical structure. Notes that using autoref will create random cells with serial number and
///      prefix 'A', e.g. A0 A01 A02 ..., and it is possible to create same cell name with different
///      contents in different runs. So you must rename duplicate cells when merging dummy gds into original gds.
///      Do not directly append, overwrite,or ignore duplicate cells -- otherwire you would get troubles.
///      If you use OASIS format to output dummy file, please disable both USE_AREF and USE_AUTOREF options.
///
///  (5) #DEFINE FILL_SRDOD_SRDPO :
///      By default, this option is enabled to insert MOS-like patterns, SR_DOD (6;7) and SR_DPO(17;7) near devices.
///
///  (6) #DEFINE FILL_TCD_PATTERN :
///      Enable this option to insert front-end dummy TCD patterns for OD/PO intra-die
///      CD control and improvement.  The front-end dummy TCD patterns include following layers:
///      NW(3;0), OD(6;0), PO(17;0), CPO(17;11), PP(25,0), NP(26;0), PMET(205;6),
///      ODBLK(150;20), POBLK(150;21), TCDDMY(165;1), TCDDMY_FH(165;6), TCDDMY_FV(165;7).
///      Customer needs to remark the TCDDMY usage in STI form and e-Tapeout.
///      If customer wants to use P&R tool to place dummy TCD patterns into chip,
///      please comment the line as below to disable this option:
///
///          //#DEFINE FILL_TCD_PATTERN
///
///  (7) #DEFINE InsideINDDMY_HD_MD
///      By default, InsideINDDMY_HD_MD option is enabled to fill DOD/DPO inside INDDMY_HD/INDDMY_MD.
///
///  (8) #DEFINE FILL_DOD_DPO :
///      By default, this option is enabled to insert Standard cell-like patterns, DOD(6;1) and DPO(17;1) into the whole chip.
///
///  (9) #DEFINE TOP_Mn
///      Turn on to connect TOP metal to AP
///
///  (10) #DEFINE COMBINE_DODPO_DMVIA :
///      Dummy OD/PO utility and dummy Metal/Via utility can be combined to get a single utility file,
///      which can insert DOD/DPO/DM/DVIA at the same time. Please be sure to complete the following
///      procedures for correct usage of the single dummy OD/PO/Metal/Via deck.
///
///      1. Please download the most update dummy OD/PO and dummy Metal/Via utility file.
///         "Dummy_FEOL_Calibre_22nm_001.13a" (version may be varied!) from TSMC-online.
///         "Dummy_BEOL_Calibre_22nm_001.13a" (version may be varied!) from TSMC-online.
///
///      2. Use the unix command 'cat' to create this single dummy OD/PO/Metal/Via deck.
///         (assuming % is the unix prompt):
///
///         % cat Dummy_FEOL_Calibre_22nm_001.13a Dummy_BEOL_Calibre_22nm_001.13a
///           > Dummy_FEOL_BEOL_Calibre_22nm_001.13a
///
///      3. The environment setups - LAYOUT PATH/LAYOUT PRIMARY/DRC RESULTS DATABASE/DRC SUMMARY REPORT,
///         and option setups - ChipWindowUsed/dmOnCorner must be set in dummy OD/PO utility file.
///         These setups in dummy Metal/Via utility file will be invalid.
///
///  (11) #DEFINE USE_SD_VOLTAGE_ON_CORE_TO_IO_NET
///   	   Turn on to use S/D voltage on net without voltage text/marker and connect to IO & core MOS simultaneously
///
///  (12) #DEFINE USE_IO_VOLTAGE_ON_CORE_TO_IO_NET
///       Turn on to use IO voltage on net without voltage marker and connect to IO & core MOS simultaneously

///**************************************************************************************
///      NOTE:
///**************************************************************************************
/// If this utility was used for cell level design, please set the options or variables below.
///
/// 1. Cell boundary: turn on option "ChipWindowUsed" to define cell boundary or use whole
///                   layout extent.
/// 2. Dummy on cell corner: turn on option "dmOnCorner" to insert dummy on cell corner.
/// 3. Dummy to cell boundary: variable "D2CHIP" defines min. space between dummy and cell
///    boundary, user can revise this variable to change the space between dummy and cell
///    boundary. Note that dummy OD/PO must be enclosed by chip edge >= 0.6um. (SR_DOD.EN.2/DOD.EN.2/SR_DPO.EN.5/DPO.EN.1)
///**************************************************************************************













/* SWITCH DEFINITION START */

//   ENVIRONMENT SETUP
//-----------------------
PRECISION    1000
RESOLUTION      5                               // tool resolution

LAYOUT SYSTEM GDSII
LAYOUT PATH "../../backup/signoff/mxu_top_postSignoff.gds2"                       // GDS file name
LAYOUT PRIMARY "mxu_top"                    // top cell name
//DRC RESULTS DATABASE "DODPO.gds" GDSII          // Output topcell name is the same as the original layout,
                                                // please do not stream-in to the library of original design.
DRC RESULTS DATABASE "../../backup/signoff/DODPO.gds" GDSII _DODPO // Output topcell name will be suffixed by _DODPO
DRC SUMMARY REPORT "DODPO.sum"
DRC MAXIMUM RESULTS ALL
DRC KEEP EMPTY NO
//LAYOUT ALLOW DUPLICATE CELL YES
//LAYOUT ERROR ON INPUT NO

//******* User defined chip area  **************************************
//#DEFINE UseprBoundary     // use layer prBoundary(108) to define the chip window
//#DEFINE ChipWindowUsed    // use specified coordinate to define the chip window
VARIABLE xLB   0.0          // x-coordinate of left-bottom corner for user defined chip window
VARIABLE yLB   0.0          // y-coordinate of left-bottom corner for user defined chip window
VARIABLE xRT   1000.0       // x-coordinate of right-top corner for user defined chip window
VARIABLE yRT   1000.0       // y-coordinate of right-top corner for user defined chip window
LAYER ChipWindow 500        // layer number for constructing chip boundary

//******* Option for chip corner empty area definition ***********************
#DEFINE dmOnCorner        // turn on to insert dummy inside Chip Corner (apply to cell or macro level design)
//#DEFINE WithSealring      // already with the sealring structure assembled?

//******* Options for output structure ****************
#DEFINE USE_AREF            // use AREF output
//#DEFINE USE_AUTOREF       // use AUTOREF output
VARIABLE PRE_FIX "TSMC"     // output cell name prefix when using AUTOREF output

//******* Select patterns to be filled ******************************************
#DEFINE FILL_SRDOD_SRDPO    // insert MOS-like patterns / SR_DOD / SR_DPO
#DEFINE FILL_TCD_PATTERN    // insert dummy TCD patterns
#DEFINE FILL_DOD_DPO        // insert Standard cell-like patterns / DOD / DPO / PP
#DEFINE InsideINDDMY_HD_MD  // insert DOD/DPO inside INDDMY_HD/INDDMY_MD

//#DEFINE COMBINE_DODPO_DMVIA // combine dummy OD/PO and dummy Metal/Via utilities
//#DEFINE TOP_M5                      // Connect TOP metal M5 to AP
//#DEFINE TOP_M6                      // Connect TOP metal M6 to AP
#DEFINE TOP_M7                      // Connect TOP metal M7 to AP
//#DEFINE TOP_M8                      // Connect TOP metal M8 to AP
//#DEFINE TOP_M9                      // Connect TOP metal M9 to AP
//#DEFINE TOP_M10                      // Connect TOP metal M10 to AP
//#DEFINE TOP_M11                      // Connect TOP metal M11 to AP
//#DEFINE TOP_M12                      // Connect TOP metal M12 to AP
//#DEFINE TOP_M13                      // Connect TOP metal M13 to AP
//#DEFINE USE_SD_VOLTAGE_ON_CORE_TO_IO_NET  // Turn on to use S/D voltage on net without voltage text/marker and connect to IO & core MOS simultaneously
//#DEFINE USE_IO_VOLTAGE_ON_CORE_TO_IO_NET  // Turn on to use IO voltage on net without voltage marker and connect to IO & core MOS simultaneously

/* SWITCH DEFINITION END */

//***** Layer Assignment ******************

LAYER DNWi       10000     // deep-nwell
LAYER MAP 1 DATATYPE 0 10000

LAYER NWii      3000            // nwell technology
LAYER MAP 3 DATATYPE 0 3000

LAYER NWiOTHERS 3001
LAYER MAP 3 DATATYPE >=1   <=129 3001
LAYER MAP 3 DATATYPE >=150 <=169 3001
LAYER MAP 3 DATATYPE >=180 <=255 3001

LAYER NWLVTi    1671            // LVT NWELL for N28HPA process
LAYER MAP 167 DATATYPE 1 1671

NWi = NWii OR NWLVTi

LAYER PMi        5050     // Polymide (if drawn)
LAYER MAP 5 DATATYPE 0 5050

LAYER ODi 350
LAYER MAP 6 DATATYPE 0           350

LAYER ODiRFDRAIN 351
LAYER MAP 6 DATATYPE 3 351      // for mixed-mode process to recognize RF MOS region

LAYER ODiSRAM   352
LAYER MAP 6 DATATYPE >=11 <=20 352  // for SRAM only

LAYER ODiOTHERS  353
LAYER MAP 6 DATATYPE >=4   <=6     353
LAYER MAP 6 DATATYPE >=8   <=10    353
LAYER MAP 6 DATATYPE >=21  <=32    353
LAYER MAP 6 DATATYPE >=34  <=129   353
LAYER MAP 6 DATATYPE >=150 <=169   353
LAYER MAP 6 DATATYPE >=180 <=255   353
LAYER MAP 7 DATATYPE >=0   <=129   353
LAYER MAP 7 DATATYPE >=150 <=169   353
LAYER MAP 7 DATATYPE >=180 <=255   353
LAYER MAP 8 DATATYPE >=0   <=129   353
LAYER MAP 8 DATATYPE >=150 <=169   353
LAYER MAP 8 DATATYPE >=180 <=255   353

LAYER DOD       354
LAYER MAP 6 DATATYPE 1 354      // Mapping (6;1) to 353 for dummy OD

LAYER SRDOD     357
LAYER MAP 6 DATATYPE 7 357      // Mapping (6;7) to 357 for SRDOD


LAYER POi       364
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE 0           364

LAYER POiSRAM 365
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE >=12 <=20 365 // for SRAM only

LAYER POiOTHERS 366
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE >=3    <=6   366
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE >=8    <=10  366
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE >=21   <=30  366
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE >=32   <=50  366
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE >=52   <=129 366
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE >=150  <=169 366
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE >=180  <=255 366

LAYER DPO       361
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE 1 361     // Mapping (17;1) to 361 for dummy PO

LAYER SRDPO     367
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE 7 367     // Mapping (17;7) to 367 for SRDPO

LAYER CPO       1711
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE 11 1711

LAYER CPO_SRM 1712
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE 12 1712

LAYER mVTLi     362             // Used to generate poly logical operation in LVT process
LAYER MAP 17 DATATYPE 51 362    // Mapping (17;51, layer PO, purpose rule1) to 362 for mVTLi


LAYER NTNi      11000           // Native NMOS blocked implant
LAYER MAP 11 DATATYPE 0 11000

LAYER NCapNTNi  11020           // connected NMOS capacitors within same NT_N region
LAYER MAP 11 DATATYPE 20 11020

LAYER VTZ_N     11200           // NT_N region
LAYER MAP 11 DATATYPE 200 11200

LAYER VTLNi      1200    // 1.0V Low Vt NMOS Implant
LAYER MAP 12 DATATYPE 0 1200
LAYER VTL_N25i      1202    // VTL_N25,Isolation and dedicated IOPW implant define at LVT NMOS(2.5V)
LAYER MAP 12 DATATYPE 2 1202
LAYER VTLPi      1300   // 1.0V Low Vt PMOS Implant
LAYER MAP 13 DATATYPE 0 1300
LAYER VTL_P25i      1302   // Isolation and dedicated IONW implant define at LVT PMOS(2.5V)
LAYER MAP 13 DATATYPE 2 1302
LAYER OD33i      1500    // define 3.3V thick gate oxides
LAYER MAP 15 DATATYPE 0 1500

LAYER OD18i     1600            // define 1.8V thick gate oxides
LAYER MAP 16 DATATYPE 0         1600

LAYER OD25i     1800            // define 2.5V thick gate oxides
LAYER MAP 18 DATATYPE 0 1800

LAYER OD15i     2100            // define 1.5V thick gate oxides
LAYER MAP 21 DATATYPE 0 2100

LAYER OD_HG     16111           // define Horizontal gate devices
LAYER MAP 161 DATATYPE 11 16111

OD2 = (((OD33i OR OD18i) OR OD25i) OR OD15i) OR OD_HG

LAYER OD2533    451             // define 2.5V thick gate oxides overdrive 3.3v
LAYER MAP 18 DATATYPE 3 451

LAYER OD2518    452             // define 2.5V thick gate oxides underdrive 1.8v
LAYER MAP 18 DATATYPE 4 452

LAYER PPi        2500		// P+ S/D implant
LAYER MAP 25 DATATYPE 0 2500
LAYER NPi        2600		// N+ S/D implant
LAYER MAP 26 DATATYPE 0 2600
LAYER RPOi       2900		// Silicided Block Layer
LAYER MAP 29 DATATYPE 0 2900 

LAYER COii       3010		// Define connect for M1 to S/D and Gate
LAYER MAP 30 DATATYPE  0 3010

LAYER CO_VIRT 3030
LAYER MAP 30 DATATYPE 30 3030

COi = OR COii CO_VIRT	

LAYER COPUSH    3011            // rule pushed contact in SRAM cell
LAYER MAP 30 DATATYPE 11 3011

LAYER COiSRAM   3012
LAYER MAP 30 DATATYPE >=11 <=22 3012

LAYER COiOTHERS 3013
LAYER MAP 30 DATATYPE >=1  <=10  3013
LAYER MAP 30 DATATYPE >=23  <=29  3013
LAYER MAP 30 DATATYPE >=31  <=129 3013
LAYER MAP 30 DATATYPE >=150 <=169 3013
LAYER MAP 30 DATATYPE >=180 <=255 3013
LAYER M1i       3100          // Metal1 layer
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE  0 3100
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE  7 3100
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 10 3100
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 20 3100
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 27 3100
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 30 3100
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 40 3100
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 50 3100
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 57 3100
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 60 3100
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 80 3100

LAYER M1_n06n12Vi 1181        // Metal1 -0.6V~-1.2V Marker Layer
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE >179  <= 180 1181

LAYER M1_n01n05Vi 1161        // Metal1 -0.1V~-0.5V Marker Layer
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE >189  <= 190 1161

LAYER M1_0012Vi   1021        // Metal1 0.1V~1.2V Marker Layer
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE >=200 <= 212 1021

LAYER M1_1317Vi   1041        // Metal1 1.3V~1.7V Marker Layer
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE >=213 <= 217 1041

LAYER M1_1825Vi   1061        // Metal1 1.8V~2.5V Marker Layer
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE >=218 <= 219 1061

LAYER M1_33Vi     1081        // Metal1 3.3V Marker Layer
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE >219  <= 220 1081

LAYER M1_5Vi      1101        // Metal1 5V Marker Layer
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE >220  <= 221 1101

LAYER M1_65Vi      1221        // Metal1 6.5V Marker Layer
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 226 1221
LAYER M1_55Vi      1261        // Metal1 5.5V Marker Layer
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 235 1261
LAYER M1_1833Vi   1121        // Metal1 1.8V~3.3V Marker Layer
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE >=218 <= 220 1121

LAYER M1_1517Vi   1141        // Metal1 1.5V~1.7V Marker Layer
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE >=215 <= 217 1141

LAYER M1_1233Vi   961
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE >=212 <= 220 961

LAYER M1_0011Vi   901
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE >=200 <= 211 901

LAYER DUM1      3101          // dummy Metal1
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE  1 3101
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 11 3101
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 21 3101
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 31 3101
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 41 3101
LAYER MAP 31 DATATYPE 51 3101
